The paper focuses on path planning for an unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) in precision agriculture, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use case of weed detection involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The algorithm also involves optimization (cs.AI) and dynamic constraints (cs.SY).
